# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ARGUS environment variables
# Copy to .env.local for local dev, or set these in Vercel
# (Project → Settings → Environment Variables) for Preview + Production.
# Never commit real keys.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# LLM provider: "gemini" (default, free) or "anthropic"
LLM_PROVIDER=gemini

# Optional model override (defaults: gemini → gemini-2.5-flash, anthropic → claude-opus-4-8)
# LLM_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# Google Gemini — free key, no card: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Anthropic — only needed if LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Langfuse observability (optional; cloud free tier or self-host)
# LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY=
# LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY=
# LANGFUSE_BASEURL=https://cloud.langfuse.com

# ── Optional tool keys ───────────────────────────────────────
# Most gather tools are keyless (Wikipedia, company site, job boards,
# GDELT news, SEC EDGAR). These only enable extra tools when present.

# Finnhub — free financial-markets data: https://finnhub.io/register
# Without it, the financial-markets tool simply no-ops.
# FINNHUB_API_KEY=

# SEC EDGAR User-Agent — optional. SEC fair-access wants a contact email in the
# UA; a sensible non-personal default ships in code. Override to use your own
# contact, e.g. "ARGUS (you@example.com)".
# EDGAR_USER_AGENT=

# GitHub — optional. The GitHub tool works unauthenticated but is rate-limited to
# 60 requests/hour per IP; a token (classic or fine-grained, no scopes needed for
# public data) raises that to 5000/hour. https://github.com/settings/tokens
# GITHUB_TOKEN=
